02:03.020 --> 02:05.740
Kelly Maguire.

02:11.060 --> 02:12.579
Said I'll be there in five.

02:12.580 --> 02:16.419
Tell me what you're wearing.
Sick! Where are you rubbing it?

02:16.420 --> 02:19.019
Go on, girl! Turn it to the highest,
let me hear you.

02:19.020 --> 02:20.100
You're getting me at it now.

02:20.101 --> 02:22.179
He's got my bag! He's got my bag!

02:22.180 --> 02:23.540
He's got my bag!

02:25.340 --> 02:27.259
Push it all the way up.

02:27.260 --> 02:30.499
I bet it's nice! Now pinch
your nipples and shout my name.

02:30.500 --> 02:32.779
Hope it's not your mum
or sister next.

02:32.780 --> 02:34.660
Yeah, they wouldn't be out
on their own!

02:34.661 --> 02:38.300
No nothing. I'm coming.
Not in my pants! Just wait there.

02:39.900 --> 02:40.940
Arrggh! Help!

02:42.500 --> 02:44.659
Will somebody give me a hand?

02:44.660 --> 02:47.219
I'm a policeman!
Look, somebody give me hand!

02:47.220 --> 02:48.458
Help!

02:48.459 --> 02:49.420
Someone help!

02:51.580 --> 02:53.539
Yeah, ambulance.

02:53.540 --> 02:56.619
His leg's impaled on a fence.
Look, will someone give us a hand?

02:56.620 --> 02:58.339
PHONE RINGS

02:58.340 --> 02:59.820
Don't get involved, mate.

02:59.821 --> 03:01.180
Gallagher!

03:04.940 --> 03:06.620
Yeah, I'm almost there.

03:10.940 --> 03:13.859
"With love and respect
for the woman I worship,

03:13.860 --> 03:15.979
"and whose family
I'm privileged to enter.

03:15.980 --> 03:20.059
"I pledge to guide
her beautiful child..."

03:20.060 --> 03:21.980
Maybe doing our own vows
is a bad idea?

03:21.981 --> 03:24.579
Mimi's keen you stamp your own style
on this wedding.

03:24.580 --> 03:26.180
She'll do a good job with hers.

03:26.181 --> 03:28.379
The lads'll think
I'm taking the piss.

03:28.380 --> 03:31.739
So focus more on your love for Mimi.

03:31.740 --> 03:32.860
But, bottom line,

03:32.861 --> 03:35.779
you are going to be
their step-father.

03:35.780 --> 03:36.979
Mam?

03:36.980 --> 03:38.060
She's in the Jockey.

03:38.061 --> 03:40.579
Just had to give Scouse Macka a slap.
Spreading lies.

03:40.580 --> 03:44.099
Said that Dalglish and Souness
spit-roasted the night

03:44.100 --> 03:46.699
them tramps won the European Cup!
She hates Jocks.

03:46.700 --> 03:48.259
Maybe that's why.

03:48.260 --> 03:48.938
What yous up to?

03:48.939 --> 03:50.220
Private tuition.

03:50.221 --> 03:52.259
Thought you got maths?

03:52.260 --> 03:53.300
Everyone can improve.

03:53.301 --> 03:56.539
It's so I can help out with
invoices, spreadsheets.

03:56.540 --> 03:57.378
Duh! We don't keep paper trails.

03:57.379 --> 03:58.778
The Jockey has to.

03:58.779 --> 04:00.220
Tax returns.

04:00.221 --> 04:02.060
Karen does all that.

04:05.900 --> 04:07.499
"I promise to love,

04:07.500 --> 04:09.019
"cherish

04:09.020 --> 04:11.099
"and mentor these beautiful children

04:11.100 --> 04:12.499
"James, Shane,

04:12.500 --> 04:14.020
"Michael and Cilla."

04:22.780 --> 04:25.740
"I was the sad song
you made better...

04:27.780 --> 04:29.780
"..said don't be afraid
of the dark..."

04:31.740 --> 04:33.499
Fucking knew it!

04:33.500 --> 04:35.539
Mam and that granny-shagger!

04:35.540 --> 04:36.660
Et tu, Rooney!

04:38.140 --> 04:39.899
He's got a name.

04:39.900 --> 04:41.579
Yeah?

04:41.580 --> 04:43.699
What's the opposite of paedophile?

04:43.700 --> 04:44.740
Paedophobe.

04:47.740 --> 04:48.898
I'm sorry, Mimi.

04:48.899 --> 04:50.620
Someone going to tell us
what's going on?

04:50.621 --> 04:55.019
I wanted a more fitting occasion
for the announcement.

04:55.020 --> 04:58.540
But I suppose the more time to get
your head round it is no bad thing.

05:00.140 --> 05:02.620
Billy Tutton is doing me the honour
of making me his wife.

05:05.500 --> 05:07.180
Who's Billy Tutton?

05:10.700 --> 05:11.980
No congratulations?

05:13.860 --> 05:16.699
A match made
in Jeremy Kyle ratings heaven!

05:16.700 --> 05:19.259
May you have a gilf-edged future!

05:19.260 --> 05:23.020
No three cheers
for the happy couple?

05:24.300 --> 05:27.059
Bet a round of drinks on the house
will break the ice.

05:27.060 --> 05:29.379
On me.

05:29.380 --> 05:30.340
CHEERING

05:45.140 --> 05:46.260
I didn't get rid of it.

05:46.261 --> 05:48.139
So lay off the vodka!

05:48.140 --> 05:50.819
I swore I'd never be a single mum.

05:50.820 --> 05:53.260
You don't know what he'll say.
Shane loves kids.

05:53.261 --> 05:54.979
It's got nothing to do with him.

05:54.980 --> 05:55.620
How can it not?

05:55.621 --> 05:58.739
He's always trying to be nice.
Makes my skin crawl.

05:58.740 --> 06:00.020
Bit harsh.

06:00.021 --> 06:05.259
All that natural, earthy shit
used to turn me on.

06:05.260 --> 06:06.860
I was thrilled he was so different.

06:06.861 --> 06:08.739
Now he just stinks.

06:08.740 --> 06:10.900
Your emotions are bound to be
all over the place.

06:10.901 --> 06:13.940
You know when you know.
I've moved on.

06:20.900 --> 06:22.018
I hate this park.

06:22.019 --> 06:23.300
Even with me to protect you?

06:24.540 --> 06:27.379
Where were those shitbags
when they were needed?

06:27.380 --> 06:29.939
Eww! Check PC Plod
shaking his daft head!

06:29.940 --> 06:31.740
Bet you feel safe
with him at night(!)

06:31.741 --> 06:34.619
Carl's ten times the man
you'll ever be!

06:34.620 --> 06:35.898
Carl?

06:35.899 --> 06:37.380
I think he knows.

06:37.381 --> 06:40.979
Takes more than Armani jeans
and a pair of Air Max to be a man.

06:40.980 --> 06:41.778
Eh, Gallagher?

06:41.779 --> 06:42.900
Stand up for yourself!

06:45.140 --> 06:47.739
Do you two wash the filth
off each other in the shower?

06:47.740 --> 06:48.980
Leave it.

06:50.020 --> 06:51.260
D'you know him?

06:51.261 --> 06:53.619
I think so.

06:53.620 --> 06:55.299
Simon...

06:55.300 --> 06:56.699
Wexford?

06:56.700 --> 06:58.339
In our kid's year in school.

06:58.340 --> 06:59.820
Ian? Lip.

07:00.940 --> 07:02.699
Good at football?

07:02.700 --> 07:05.099
Brilliant. City's academy.

07:05.100 --> 07:07.139
Not that good, then.

07:07.140 --> 07:10.779
I vote we choke him on his own
bollocks, slice him like a pizza,

07:10.780 --> 07:14.499
and feed him to the eels
in the Manchester Ship Canal.

07:14.500 --> 07:17.219
Ah! Curious face of
Billy Tutton Button!

07:17.220 --> 07:19.179
I'll get him on his own.

07:19.180 --> 07:20.979
Have a word.

07:20.980 --> 07:22.299
Imagine it's you or him,

07:22.300 --> 07:24.859
dead or alive,
but there can only be one winner.

07:24.860 --> 07:26.419
All right, calm down!

07:26.420 --> 07:29.659
Or, right, he's ripped you off
for fifty grand. Nobheads!

07:29.660 --> 07:31.420
We can't kill him for marrying Mum.

07:31.421 --> 07:32.979
Pussies.

07:32.980 --> 07:34.900
We make the little shit realise
this can't happen.

07:34.901 --> 07:37.499
Send him far away, if necessary.

07:37.500 --> 07:39.019
And what if she follows him?

07:39.020 --> 07:40.058
Then at least we've done our best.

07:40.059 --> 07:41.378
Have you heard yourselves?

07:41.379 --> 07:42.100
Earwigging!

07:42.101 --> 07:45.459
Surprises are nice, but I
don't want you spending too much.

07:45.460 --> 07:49.499
Our love for each other
is everything we need.

07:49.500 --> 07:53.099
D'you reckon, Mimi? A few brothers
and sisters might be nice for Cilla.

07:53.100 --> 07:55.419
We'll have to get a move on.

07:55.420 --> 07:57.660
That's what it's all about, Mimi.

08:00.740 --> 08:03.339
Maybe some day you'll
get a grip of your bird.

08:03.340 --> 08:05.059
Billy!

08:05.060 --> 08:06.180
I need a word.

08:06.181 --> 08:09.380
I can't, mate, sorry. I've got to
go see a man about a horse.

08:21.800 --> 08:24.080
Me and Paddy turned the
tables on the greedy fucks

08:24.081 --> 08:26.359
- Started drinking in
this hotel weeks before,

08:26.360 --> 08:28.480
spent plenty,
got the manager sweet...

08:28.481 --> 08:32.159
Night of the wedding, promised
we'd pay the tab at the end...

08:32.159 --> 08:37.198
free bar, everyone proper drunk.
We just did one ... never went back.

08:37.200 --> 08:38.999
Why don't we do that?

08:39.000 --> 08:41.839
Cameras, too many grasses ...
it's tricky now.

08:41.840 --> 08:45.639
I hope I make you
as happy as Paddy did.

08:45.640 --> 08:47.160
Oh, of course you do...

08:48.200 --> 08:50.320
and then some, handsome.

08:57.120 --> 08:59.200
Did you bait many badgers,
Daisy Crockett?

08:59.201 --> 09:03.119
Lovely. Keep us cosy this winter.

09:03.120 --> 09:04.880
Make a nice hat and mittens them.

09:04.881 --> 09:06.599
You all right in there?

09:06.600 --> 09:08.159
It's easier to concentrate.

09:08.160 --> 09:10.680
Did you ask Chesney
about the food?

09:16.320 --> 09:18.080
What?

09:22.240 --> 09:25.359
You know Jamie won't
let this happen don't you?

09:25.360 --> 09:28.319
And we all have to
follow our leader.

09:28.320 --> 09:30.360
I can't do dead things any more.

09:41.840 --> 09:43.400
I thought we were doing all right.

09:43.401 --> 09:46.160
I'm sorry, Shane.

09:49.160 --> 09:50.318
I can't be with you.

09:50.319 --> 09:52.200
After everything we've been through?

09:52.201 --> 09:56.759
Years of ups, downs,
spinning round and fucking round...?

09:56.760 --> 09:59.839
What's so big that
we can't deal with it now?

09:59.840 --> 10:03.439
It's not about
the big stuff any more.

10:03.440 --> 10:05.520
Is it that bald fucker?

10:07.520 --> 10:11.759
Slag. Wanker, wanker!

10:11.760 --> 10:14.119
Come on! I can do that.

10:14.120 --> 10:16.160
Bad taste, Shane.

10:19.680 --> 10:21.160
Are you going to him?

10:21.161 --> 10:24.119
I'm going to no-one.

10:24.120 --> 10:26.280
There is no-one.

10:28.440 --> 10:29.480
Then what?

10:30.680 --> 10:33.999
The fact that there almost was...

10:34.000 --> 10:36.600
means you can't be the one any more.

10:45.680 --> 10:48.199
I promise.

10:48.200 --> 10:50.040
I promise I will make this better.

10:50.041 --> 10:53.719
Don't...

10:53.720 --> 10:56.599
No more hunting, if that helps.

10:56.600 --> 10:58.799
Kel, I swear to God. Watch me.

10:58.800 --> 11:00.198
Now that I know how you feel...

11:00.199 --> 11:01.198
You don't know how I feel.

11:01.199 --> 11:02.600
Yes! Yes I do.

11:04.640 --> 11:10.080
Kelly, I swear I'll fix us.

11:12.280 --> 11:15.920
Give me one more chance to show you.
That's all I need.

11:20.360 --> 11:22.120
I'll show you...

11:25.040 --> 11:28.799
Three Rolexes, two Tags, a Panerai
and a bird's Cartier. Suit Karen.

11:28.800 --> 11:32.799
These things are worth
a third without their papers.

11:32.800 --> 11:35.359
Not these. Phil Fingerarse said
he'll take the lot at 40%.

11:35.360 --> 11:39.239
Bit of a coincidence Baghead Billy's
just back from Bangkok.

11:39.240 --> 11:42.119
These are real, dickhead.
The ram raids were on the news.

11:42.120 --> 11:43.840
You couldn't raid a biscuit tin.

11:43.841 --> 11:45.279
Not me!

11:45.280 --> 11:46.720
(WHISTLE)

11:52.760 --> 11:53.880
What you doing here?

11:53.881 --> 11:56.000
Any chance of a chat...?

11:57.680 --> 11:59.480
Don't I know you from somewhere?

12:06.080 --> 12:07.040
Am I in trouble?

12:10.200 --> 12:11.000
Still playing football?

12:11.001 --> 12:14.799
Bit of five-a-side. You?

12:14.800 --> 12:16.520
Got a game with
the national police team.

12:16.521 --> 12:19.399
Wouldn't thought you'd make it.

12:19.400 --> 12:22.239
Went for different kinds
of trials instead.

12:22.240 --> 12:25.079
I know I should have done
something... in the park.

12:25.080 --> 12:26.879
Don't worry about it.

12:26.880 --> 12:29.919
Official policy is
discourage have-a-go-heroes.

12:29.920 --> 12:31.878
Gives us more paperwork
if a robbery becomes a murder.

12:31.879 --> 12:33.798
Like you said,
that could've been my mam.

12:33.799 --> 12:35.200
Should have left him stuck there.

12:35.201 --> 12:38.279
Yeah, well... he'll never
be a father, but he's alive.

12:38.280 --> 12:43.319
I never forget a bizzie's kipper.
Crown court two years ago.

12:43.320 --> 12:45.560
You put Vinny the Red
away for five years.

12:45.561 --> 12:48.199
And I'm sure you and Paddy
looked after his family.

12:48.200 --> 12:50.839
Only right,
seeing as he kept his mouth shut...

12:50.840 --> 12:54.119
Buzzing you asked, mate.
Just... you know...

12:54.120 --> 12:57.319
Soon as I get the cartilage fixed,
I'll definitely give you a call.

12:57.320 --> 12:59.360
Be good to play
for a proper team again...

13:14.280 --> 13:15.680
He's pressing charges.

13:15.681 --> 13:17.279
For what?

13:17.280 --> 13:20.039
Said I pulled his
leg down on the spike. Deliberately.

13:20.040 --> 13:21.878
It's now my fault
he can't have kids.

13:21.879 --> 13:23.038
Bollocks.

13:23.039 --> 13:25.360
Agreed. But if this goes
the wrong way, I could go to jail.

13:25.361 --> 13:26.999
On some smackhead's say-so?

13:27.000 --> 13:29.439
I've had something similar before.

13:29.440 --> 13:34.720
I know it's hardly second nature,
but I could do with a witness.

13:36.200 --> 13:38.879
Or are you going to turn away again?

13:38.880 --> 13:41.199
I don't think you understand.

13:41.200 --> 13:45.080
You know what? I really do.

13:52.720 --> 13:56.880
You having a laugh?
Gonna play football with a dibble?

14:03.240 --> 14:05.439
Need a lift?

14:05.440 --> 14:06.840
I'm not going far.

14:06.841 --> 14:08.759
It's all right, Billy, get in.

14:08.760 --> 14:10.680
I've got to go and see the florist.

14:15.320 --> 14:17.280
I've got a few knock-off dresses...

14:17.281 --> 14:21.239
need you to pick one for Mimi ...
it'll just take a minute...

14:21.240 --> 14:22.480
Maybe later, mate.

14:30.000 --> 14:31.600
Grab him!

14:34.000 --> 14:38.079
Fuck's sake!
What's up with you?!

14:38.080 --> 14:39.358
Sorry.

14:39.359 --> 14:40.320
You OK?

14:42.160 --> 14:43.120
Get in.

14:54.800 --> 14:56.000
Hang on, Tony!

14:56.001 --> 14:57.800
Fucking hell...

14:59.600 --> 15:03.440
Right. Get in here and bend over,
you worthless piece of shi...

15:05.600 --> 15:07.600
Tony doesn't mind.

15:09.680 --> 15:11.800
Won't be long.

15:14.520 --> 15:17.559
Bit kinky. Much demand?

15:17.560 --> 15:18.560
You've no idea.

15:20.200 --> 15:22.919
I just almost ran our Shane over.

15:22.920 --> 15:24.839
He's in bits.

15:24.840 --> 15:27.919
Feel guilty about fucking
your mum's relationship

15:27.920 --> 15:29.919
so you want to fix your brother's?

15:29.920 --> 15:33.879
I don't need some headcase going
under when we're out grafting.

15:33.880 --> 15:37.039
Again, all about you.
The law according to Jamie Maguire.

15:37.040 --> 15:39.279
It's not just about me

15:39.280 --> 15:43.320
if some ex-smackhead brass
is taking the piss out of my family.

15:47.520 --> 15:49.160
Please leave.

15:54.040 --> 15:55.360
Tell me I'm wrong.

15:58.800 --> 15:59.760
Does he know?

16:03.920 --> 16:06.400
Did it get a bit messy
with some punter?

16:09.080 --> 16:10.200
Are you keeping it?

16:14.920 --> 16:17.399
No wonder you want out.

16:17.400 --> 16:19.319
It was over long before this.

16:19.320 --> 16:22.079
Yeah, well, he thinks
you're giving it another go.

16:22.080 --> 16:25.239
Yeah? If we do,
it's because we want to.

16:25.240 --> 16:26.560
KNOCKING ON DOOR

16:26.561 --> 16:28.319
When will you learn?

16:28.320 --> 16:31.559
You can't make the world
fit into the box you want.

16:31.560 --> 16:33.999
And every time you force it,

16:34.000 --> 16:38.240
it keeps straining to spring back
into the shape it was meant to be.

16:45.600 --> 16:48.280
Try not to hurt him too much.

17:00.400 --> 17:02.679
850, 9,

17:02.680 --> 17:05.279
950, two grand.

17:05.280 --> 17:09.878
Now add that to what he's
already give you.

17:09.880 --> 17:12.040
Making me give in
and let Billy think I'm a pushover?

17:12.040 --> 17:14.319
He thinks he did good, though.

17:14.319 --> 17:15.078
Three?

17:15.079 --> 17:16.160
Five.

17:16.161 --> 17:17.919
Three and a half?

17:17.920 --> 17:20.440
You can't kid a kidder.
Four and a half.

17:23.040 --> 17:25.440
My last offer... four grand.

17:31.200 --> 17:32.999
I'm grateful, Ches.

17:33.000 --> 17:34.558
I got my reputation to think of.

17:34.559 --> 17:35.918
He's just trying to prove himself.

17:35.919 --> 17:37.998
Jackson said he was
a trier at school.

17:37.999 --> 17:39.840
That's what we called
the divvies in woodwork.

17:39.841 --> 17:42.159
Don't be so sensitive, Mimi.

17:42.160 --> 17:44.279
He didn't even get that.

17:44.280 --> 17:47.519
Don't think I haven't noticed all
the sniggering behind our backs.

17:47.520 --> 17:48.920
You're being paranoid.

17:48.921 --> 17:51.639
Yeah? Hardly been inundated
with offers to help, have we?

17:51.640 --> 17:53.120
