we can go home.

36:23.360 --> 36:24.679
What's up with you?

36:24.680 --> 36:27.239
No more... I just want to go.

36:27.240 --> 36:29.839
Come on, Champ.

36:29.840 --> 36:30.480
Look... I just
want to go home!

36:30.481 --> 36:32.959
Eh? Eh?

36:32.960 --> 36:35.040
Oh!

36:38.400 --> 36:39.959
What do you reckon?

36:39.960 --> 36:41.159
Not bad.

36:41.160 --> 36:43.480
Think he's ready?

36:47.080 --> 36:48.520
Welcome to the family.

36:51.320 --> 36:54.520
Hey. You wouldn't have
put me down that easy.

36:57.880 --> 37:01.679
It's a pathetic excuse
for ordinary nobheads

37:01.680 --> 37:04.519
going bananas away from
the missus and the uprights,

37:04.520 --> 37:07.359
sniffing charlie
and shagging brass!

37:07.360 --> 37:09.679
Pitiful existence.

37:09.680 --> 37:12.800
You not get asked on
the stag-do, then, Frank?

37:13.760 --> 37:15.799
SIRENS BLARE

37:15.800 --> 37:19.079
DANCE MUSIC PLAYS

37:19.080 --> 37:21.759
(LAUGHS) Hey!
Hen-pecked already!

37:21.760 --> 37:24.959
I tell you what, he's a braver man
than me taking her on.

37:24.960 --> 37:29.519
Yeah, it's OK, but it doesn't feel
right if you're not having one.

37:29.520 --> 37:31.679
I had one the first time round.

37:31.680 --> 37:35.279
Last thing I need's a hangover
on my special day.

37:35.280 --> 37:38.279
Chesney's on his way.

37:38.280 --> 37:41.319
Enjoy yourself.
I'm all right. Don't worry.

37:41.320 --> 37:44.640
OK, then. Right, bye.

37:46.960 --> 37:49.079
Look, you sure you're OK?

37:49.080 --> 37:50.200
Course I am!

37:52.800 --> 37:56.119
Do you want one of mammy's stories?

37:56.120 --> 37:58.000
FRONT DOOR CLOSES

37:59.640 --> 38:03.799
About a princess
who waited half her life

38:03.800 --> 38:05.959
to find a real prince charming?

38:05.960 --> 38:08.919
KNOCKING ON FRONT DOOR

38:08.920 --> 38:10.720
Keep your fucking hat on!

38:14.720 --> 38:16.159
Mimi Maguire?

38:16.160 --> 38:16.840
What's it to you?

38:16.841 --> 38:20.479
I'm arresting you for wilful neglect
of your duties as the hen,

38:20.480 --> 38:23.119
on the orders of your friends
and neighbours.

38:23.120 --> 38:26.239
Ha-ha! You didn't think
you'd get away with it that easy?

38:26.240 --> 38:28.880
CHEERING

38:31.880 --> 38:34.160
CHEERING CONTINUES,
MUSIC PLAYS

38:46.440 --> 38:48.160
Here, don't encourage...

38:57.080 --> 38:59.760
DANCE MUSIC DROWNS OUT SPEECH

39:09.360 --> 39:10.080
What are you playing at?

39:10.081 --> 39:12.319
No harm in giving him
one final test.

39:12.320 --> 39:15.599
He's been on the steds over a week,
we'll be lucky if he doesn't

39:15.600 --> 39:19.639
smash this gaff up and try and rape
half the birds in here as it is!

39:19.640 --> 39:22.680
I want to see how committed
he really is.

39:29.360 --> 39:30.360
No complaints.

39:30.361 --> 39:32.240
Mum's the word, eh?

39:42.600 --> 39:45.839
MUSIC PLAYS IN THE OTHER ROOM

39:45.840 --> 39:49.479
♪ TAKE THAT:
Shine

39:49.480 --> 39:55.279
♪ You, you're such a big star to me
You're everything I wanna be... ♪

39:55.280 --> 39:57.199
Fuck!

39:57.200 --> 40:00.559
♪ ..stuck in a hole
and I want you to get out... ♪

40:00.560 --> 40:01.320
DOOR SLAMS

40:01.321 --> 40:02.919
Carl?

40:02.920 --> 40:04.000
How are you supposed to fasten...?

40:04.001 --> 40:07.199
(SINGS ALONG) # But I know
it's time for you to leave

40:07.200 --> 40:12.239
♪ We're all just pushing along
Trying to figure it out, out, out!

40:12.240 --> 40:16.719
♪ All your anticipation
pulls you down... ♪

40:16.720 --> 40:19.959
CHURCH BELLS RING

40:19.960 --> 40:22.159
Boys, boys. John!

40:22.160 --> 40:24.479
PEOPLE CHATTER

40:24.480 --> 40:25.599
Jackson!

40:25.600 --> 40:28.920
PEOPLE GREET EACH OTHER

40:30.240 --> 40:30.800
Sound, yeah.

40:30.801 --> 40:32.559
Good luck.

40:32.560 --> 40:35.760
She's coming, she's coming!
She's coming, come on!

40:43.480 --> 40:45.360
INAUDIBLE

40:56.280 --> 40:58.080
Good luck.

41:00.520 --> 41:02.000
HORSE NEIGHS LOUDLY

41:02.001 --> 41:04.519
Dearly beloved,
we are gathered here today

41:04.520 --> 41:08.279
to celebrate the wedding
of William and Katherine.

41:08.280 --> 41:09.560
(SHE MOUTHS)

41:09.561 --> 41:14.279
Do you, Katherine Mimi
Harmonica Joy Maguire,

41:14.280 --> 41:16.399
take William Tutton
to be your husband?

41:16.400 --> 41:18.759
I do.

41:18.760 --> 41:22.319
If anyone knows
of any lawful impediment,

41:22.320 --> 41:25.360
please speak now
or forever hold your peace.

41:27.200 --> 41:30.000
COUGHING

41:32.640 --> 41:37.799
You've taught me, nurtured me,
helped me to grow and mature.

41:37.800 --> 41:41.359
I will respect and treasure you
with every atom of my being.

41:41.360 --> 41:44.559
Your precious family is now my own

41:44.560 --> 41:47.279
and I embrace them into my world.

41:47.280 --> 41:50.440
Jamie... Shane...

41:51.600 --> 41:56.279
Walk on together, I pledge
to never try to control you,

41:56.280 --> 42:00.079
to never smother you.
Trust and love will ensure

42:00.080 --> 42:03.560
we walk on our natural paths
wherever they lead us.

42:09.480 --> 42:11.520
You may now kiss the bride.

42:12.720 --> 42:16.320
CHEERING AND WHISTLING

42:25.680 --> 42:28.040
Go on, son!

42:31.040 --> 42:34.160
CHEERING CONTINUES OUTSIDE

42:41.600 --> 42:43.479
I am sorry.

42:43.480 --> 42:44.800
I know.

42:50.360 --> 42:52.719
I won't stop you any more.

42:52.720 --> 42:54.160
Thank you.

43:06.120 --> 43:08.279
CHATTER

43:08.280 --> 43:11.720
CHURCH BELLS RING

43:14.000 --> 43:16.640
HUGE CHEER

43:17.880 --> 43:19.800
CHEERING CONTINUES

43:24.480 --> 43:27.079
Billy and Mimi knew
they'd face criticism.

43:27.080 --> 43:31.519
They knew people'd disapprove,
even those closest to 'em.

43:31.520 --> 43:33.599
BOOING

43:33.600 --> 43:37.600
Regardless of this,
they've let their love lead them.

43:39.600 --> 43:41.878
They were strong enough
to stand up

43:41.879 --> 43:44.120
for what they believed in
most of all.

43:44.121 --> 43:46.639
See, they've set an example.
They've proved that

43:46.640 --> 43:50.400
you find your true direction
when you're true to yourself.

43:52.800 --> 43:54.679
Today's a very special day.

43:54.680 --> 43:59.519
And I'm proud in more ways
than you could know.

43:59.520 --> 44:01.760
Thanks for making me
your best man.

44:02.960 --> 44:04.719
CHEERING

44:04.720 --> 44:06.639
Right, a toast!

44:06.640 --> 44:09.559
To Billy and Mimi Tutton,
the bride and groom!

